VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT ^[^*/]*\b(malloc|calloc|realloc)\s*\(
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:user_input|argv|getenv|scanf|fgets|recv\s*\(|read\s*\(|atoi|atol|strtol|strtoul|input|request|len\s*\*|size\s*\*
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects usage of memory allocation functions in code.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Risky Memory Allocation: malloc() and Related Functions.
